  "prompt": "How to add a link in a Quora answer to another Quora answer when using Quora iPhone app?",
  "response": "You can add a link to another Quora answer in your answer using the Quora iPhone app, but it's not as straightforward as it is on the web version. Here's how:\n\n**1. Find the Quora Answer You Want to Link To:**\n\n*   **Navigate to the answer:** Use Quora's search or browse your feed to find the specific answer you want to reference.\n\n**2. Copy the Answer's URL (Link):**\n\n*   **Tap the \"Share\" icon:** This is usually a curved arrow pointing to the right, located beneath the answer.\n*   **Choose \"Copy Link\":**  A menu will pop up with options. Select \"Copy Link\".  This copies the full URL of that answer to your iPhone's clipboard.\n\n**3. Compose Your New Answer:**\n\n*   **Navigate to the question** you want to answer.\n*   **Tap the \"Answer\" button.** This will open the text editor for you to write your answer.\n\n**4. Paste and Format the Link in Your Answer:**\n\n*   **Paste the URL:** Tap and hold in the text field where you want the link to appear, then choose \"Paste\". This will paste the long URL.\n*   **(Recommended) Use Descriptive Text:**  It's much better to embed the link within descriptive text than to just paste the raw URL. For example:\n\n    *   **Instead of:**  \"...as you can see here: `https://www.quora.com/answer/Example-Answer`...\"\n    *   **Write:** \"...as explained in [this helpful answer](`https://www.quora.com/answer/Example-Answer`)...\"\n\n**Key Considerations When Linking:**\n\n*   **Context is Important:** Always explain *why* you're linking to the other answer. Give your readers a reason to click.\n*   **Keep it Relevant:**  Ensure the linked answer is directly relevant to the question being asked. Don't just link randomly.\n*   **Avoid Link Overload:** Don't stuff your answer with too many links. Focus on providing your own insights, and use links to supplement your answer when necessary.\n*  **Use the Markdown Text to create the link:**\n    * Put the link in brackets [ ]\n    * Then after the brackets, but the link in parenthesis ( )\n\n**Example**\n    * [This is the information you were looking for](https://www.example.com/answer/Example-Answer)\n\n**In Summary**\n\nWhile the Quora iPhone app doesn't have a dedicated \"link\" button like the web version, copying and pasting the URL is the standard way to reference other Quora answers. Remember to use descriptive text to make the link more user-friendly and provide context for your readers.\n",
